                <h1>Historical Background of Ephesians: Understanding the Context</h1>
                <p>The historical background of Ephesians provides insight into the early Christian community in Ephesus, a major city in Asia Minor. Written by the Apostle Paul, this epistle addresses themes of unity, faith, and the nature of the Church. Understanding its context and audience helps uncover its theological significance and practical applications for believers.</p>
